"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-athing-mu-is-back-on-track-paris-olympics-cover\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Days turned into weeks that stretched for months, and, still, Athing Mu didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t want to run.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 93, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 62, \"end\": 71, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athing_Mu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Athing Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athing_Mu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athing_Mu\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She had always wanted to.\", \"from\": 94, \"to\": 119, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Run harder, run faster, run past every competitor in sight.\", \"from\": 120, \"to\": 179, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not running equated to not breathing.\", \"from\": 180, \"to\": 217, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As she glided around tracks with graceful strides\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094eyes widened, mouth agape, often smiling while dominating\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094she presented an ideal, a person born to do exactly what they were doing, better than anyone else in the world.\", \"from\": 218, \"to\": 441, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That she was prodigious, medaling at the biggest, toughest races before she could legally order an alcoholic drink, only made all she accomplished seem easy, predestined.\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 613, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From her hometown of Trenton, N.J., to a worldwide stage in Tokyo, Mu set a slew of NCAA records and, in 2021,snagged a pair of Olympic golds, in the 800 meters and 4x400-meter relay.\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 797, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 635, \"end\": 642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\", \"score\": 0.8894944214207702, \"rank\": 0.1242341446081344, \"text\": \"Trenton\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\"}, {\"begin\": 674, \"end\": 679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9697248958409214, \"rank\": 0.031220297966924618, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 681, \"end\": 683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.844886024119947e-10, \"text\": \"Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\"}, {\"begin\": 698, \"end\": 702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.939813045222535e-16, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She followed it up with aworld championship medal the next summer.\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 864, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nike sponsored her.\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 884, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 865, \"end\": 869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\", \"score\": 0.9999964540765289, \"rank\": 3.5457533659245493e-06, \"text\": \"Nike\", \"types\": [\"Q728\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She dabbled in modeling.\", \"from\": 885, \"to\": 909, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Everything seemed perfect.\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 937, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But nothingthatperfect lasts.\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 967, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Weeks before the 2023 world championships in Budapest, Mu prayed she could stay home.\", \"from\": 969, \"to\": 1054, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1014, \"end\": 1022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.745023976496267e-21, \"text\": \"Budapest\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t want to run.\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1080, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just the idea of running made her anxious.\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1123, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She decided not to enter races or withdrew from them.\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1177, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her coach, Bobby Kersee,told theLos Angeles Timesa few weeks before the worlds in August 2023 that \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cthe next time [Mu] gets on the plane it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll either be on vacation or to Budapest.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d The very thing that once freed her now filled an existential dread.\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1433, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1189, \"end\": 1201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Kersee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bobby Kersee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Kersee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Kersee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The joy that defined Mu, in the best and most obvious ways, came from running, until it didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t.\", \"from\": 1435, \"to\": 1532, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1456, \"end\": 1458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.844886024119947e-10, \"text\": \"Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her agent, Alliance Sports Management CEO Rocky Arceneaux, noticed a change\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094in mood, temperature, day-to-day bearing\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094about three months before the worlds.\", \"from\": 1533, \"to\": 1691, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1544, \"end\": 1552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barisan_Nasional\", \"score\": 0.8137384841904873, \"rank\": 0.22889603899516942, \"text\": \"Alliance\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barisan_Nasional\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barisan_Nasional\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In hindsight, Arceneaux wishes he had addressed concerns earlier and more directly, like he might have, he says, with one of his NFL clients, such as Ja\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Marr Chase or Ezekiel Elliott.\", \"from\": 1692, \"to\": 1877, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1821, \"end\": 1824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"score\": 0.9999999991987352, \"rank\": 4.60281953113316e-10, \"text\": \"NFL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\"}, {\"begin\": 1847, \"end\": 1851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johnny_Marr\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1828110665930157e-31, \"text\": \"Marr\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johnny_Marr\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johnny_Marr\"}, {\"begin\": 1852, \"end\": 1857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Bank\", \"score\": 0.9999385744025593, \"rank\": 6.040317358928822e-05, \"text\": \"Chase\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Bank\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Bank\"}, {\"begin\": 1861, \"end\": 1876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ezekiel_Elliott\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ezekiel Elliott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ezekiel_Elliott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ezekiel_Elliott\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, he hesitated.\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 1900, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mu didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t skip the worlds.\", \"from\": 1902, \"to\": 1930, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She couldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t, not as the reigning Olympic and world champion in the 800.\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 2005, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She won her first heat, then fell 475 meters into her semifinal before rallying to qualify for the final.\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2111, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She even paced that medal race, until the strangest thing happened in the last 300 meters.\", \"from\": 2112, \"to\": 2202, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kenya\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Mary Moraa passed her en route to first place.\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2259, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So did Great Britain\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Keely Hodgkinson, Mu\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s chief rival, to finish second.\", \"from\": 2260, \"to\": 2340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2285, \"end\": 2301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The plummet from Olympic gold to world championship bronze was unsettling.\", \"from\": 2342, \"to\": 2416, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It happened in an instant and the result left her greatest love dimmed.\", \"from\": 2417, \"to\": 2488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThere\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s so much pressure overall,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she told reporters in Hungary.\", \"from\": 2489, \"to\": 2561, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2553, \"end\": 2560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.9999999998990461, \"rank\": 7.114220962959267e-11, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cYou\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re overthinking\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0089\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0089you know, the past few years have been a lot.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\\u00c2  Arceneaux and Kersee met with Mu immediately.\", \"from\": 2562, \"to\": 2691, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2676, \"end\": 2678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.844886024119947e-10, \"text\": \"Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t quite an intervention.\", \"from\": 2692, \"to\": 2728, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But it was necessary, serious.\", \"from\": 2729, \"to\": 2759, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They started with the truth.\", \"from\": 2760, \"to\": 2788, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They knew that she was struggling and that something wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t right.\", \"from\": 2789, \"to\": 2857, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAre you O.K.\", \"from\": 2858, \"to\": 2873, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"?\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d they asked, meaning her, the human.\", \"from\": 2873, \"to\": 2913, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mu shook her head.\", \"from\": 2915, \"to\": 2933, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No.\", \"from\": 2934, \"to\": 2937, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cShe has always been an elite runner.\", \"from\": 2938, \"to\": 2977, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She did everything with such ease and style.\", \"from\": 2978, \"to\": 3022, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was glamorous,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Arceneaux says.\", \"from\": 3023, \"to\": 3060, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t think she realized the world stage she was on.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Hence the hunt that followed, with Mu searching for what she lost, the same thing that powered her faster and faster: joy.\", \"from\": 3061, \"to\": 3247, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It felt like her career had split in half.\", \"from\": 3248, \"to\": 3290, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The fun part, the dominant, on-the-rise, broken-record-collecting portion seemed over, already, by age 21.\", \"from\": 3291, \"to\": 3397, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The not-fun part, the serious, weighted-down, can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t-lose portion, had taken hold.\", \"from\": 3398, \"to\": 3481, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She needed to merge both halves, find peace and speed simultaneously.\", \"from\": 3482, \"to\": 3551, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0089\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0089how?\", \"from\": 3552, \"to\": 3568, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Gameswere only 11 months away.\", \"from\": 3570, \"to\": 3610, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mu reached peak joy in Tokyo, at those Olympics, where she sprinted across the widest, grandest stage of her career.\", \"from\": 3612, \"to\": 3728, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3635, \"end\": 3640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9697248958409214, \"rank\": 0.031220297966924618, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Aug. 3, 2021, she became the first American woman to win 800-meter gold at the Games in more than half a century.\", \"from\": 3729, \"to\": 3845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3767, \"end\": 3781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.181772238960638e-31, \"text\": \"American woman\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She came to understand where that started, with her mindset, the absence of unnecessary internal expectations.\", \"from\": 3847, \"to\": 3957, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Japan, Mu never considered any race beyond her next one.\", \"from\": 3958, \"to\": 4017, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3961, \"end\": 3966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9935768066588219, \"rank\": 0.006464717398641564, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After qualifying for the final, she told herself,Well, may as well win.\", \"from\": 4018, \"to\": 4089, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This approach\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094low expectations yielding staggering dominance\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094made for an ideal bubble.\", \"from\": 4091, \"to\": 4181, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mu ran as if immune to pressure, ran because of how it made her feel, giving her purpose and forming her identity.\", \"from\": 4182, \"to\": 4296, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t start out running for money or fame.\", \"from\": 4297, \"to\": 4346, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She ran to win.\", \"from\": 4347, \"to\": 4362, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Because it felt good.\", \"from\": 4363, \"to\": 4384, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Because she could.\", \"from\": 4385, \"to\": 4403, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mu loved existing inside that bubble, happy and fast, each attribute powering the other.\", \"from\": 4405, \"to\": 4493, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After her individual triumph in Tokyo, she was asked to join the 4x400 relay team, a powerhouse of elite athletes including Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone and Dalilah Muhammad, formed to bolster the unprecedented medal tally of soon-to-retire Allyson Felix, long the face of U.S. track and field.\", \"from\": 4494, \"to\": 4785, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4526, \"end\": 4531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9697248958409214, \"rank\": 0.031220297966924618, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 4618, \"end\": 4624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9855093300397775e-15, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 4648, \"end\": 4664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dalilah_Muhammad\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dalilah Muhammad\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dalilah_Muhammad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dalilah_Muhammad\"}, {\"begin\": 4732, \"end\": 4745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allyson_Felix\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Allyson Felix\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allyson_Felix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allyson_Felix\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tasked with anchoring the final, Mu grabbed the baton with a sizable advantage, then took off as if shot from a cannon.\", \"from\": 4787, \"to\": 4906, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Broadcasters pronounced the race \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009call but over\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d before she sped through the first turn.\", \"from\": 4907, \"to\": 4998, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her advantage grew, widening until Mu seemed to be sprinting all by herself.\", \"from\": 4999, \"to\": 5075, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThis is when she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s most beautiful and most dangerous,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d the commentator said.\", \"from\": 5076, \"to\": 5159, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThat was like an All-Star team,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says.\", \"from\": 5161, \"to\": 5208, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll never have that again.\", \"from\": 5209, \"to\": 5242, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I mean, we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll have that again.\", \"from\": 5243, \"to\": 5275, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But it won\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t be in the same realm as what it was.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d She pauses.\", \"from\": 5276, \"to\": 5342, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe fact that I anchored was just, like\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0089\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0089man, I was running formy life.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  She finished that race roughly 50 meters ahead of anyone else.\", \"from\": 5343, \"to\": 5491, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was 19\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094on top of her sport, on top of the world.\", \"from\": 5493, \"to\": 5547, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But majestic success created new problems she never anticipated.\", \"from\": 5548, \"to\": 5612, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It changed her paradigm, this remarkable Olympic performance; the best moment of her career more like a steak knife pointed toward that ideal bubble and\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0089\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0089pop.\", \"from\": 5613, \"to\": 5778, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mu grew up in New Jersey\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s capital city, the second youngest of seven children and the first born in the U.S.\", \"from\": 5780, \"to\": 5891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her parents and her five older siblings had fled their war-torn homeland in what is now South Sudan and settled in the Garden State near relatives.\", \"from\": 5892, \"to\": 6039, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Mu (pronouncedmoe) kids traveled as a group, whether to school or church on Sundays.\", \"from\": 6040, \"to\": 6128, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But only two runners separated from the familial pack.\", \"from\": 6129, \"to\": 6183, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Athing (pronounceduh-THING) joined the Trenton Track Club at age 6, following her brother Malual, who is two years older and ran at Penn State.\", \"from\": 6185, \"to\": 6328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6224, \"end\": 6231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\", \"score\": 0.8894944214207702, \"rank\": 0.1242341446081344, \"text\": \"Trenton\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\"}, {\"begin\": 6317, \"end\": 6327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_football\", \"score\": 0.8456337228187072, \"rank\": 0.18254508142685874, \"text\": \"Penn State\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_football\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Mus sometimes struggled financially.\", \"from\": 6329, \"to\": 6369, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While family was her foundation, running faster and faster became her escape.\", \"from\": 6370, \"to\": 6447, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At 16, Mu broke the U.S. record for an indoor 600-meter race.\", \"from\": 6449, \"to\": 6510, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6456, \"end\": 6458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.844886024119947e-10, \"text\": \"Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2021, she set the U-20 world indoor record in the 800 meters.\", \"from\": 6511, \"to\": 6575, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Offers to turn pro started to flood in.\", \"from\": 6576, \"to\": 6615, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mu wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t ready, not yet.\\u00c2  No matter how fast she ran, Mu always managed to find more speed.\", \"from\": 6616, \"to\": 6711, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6674, \"end\": 6676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.844886024119947e-10, \"text\": \"Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At Trenton Central High, where she played tenor sax, made the honor roll and won a seat on the student council, she tried to have half of a normal existence: She devouredGrey\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Anatomy, dabbled in photography and interior design, joined the volunteer club.\", \"from\": 6712, \"to\": 6970, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But she wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t normal on the track; she competed for a club team rather than her high school.\", \"from\": 6971, \"to\": 7066, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She needed the competition.\", \"from\": 7067, \"to\": 7094, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She enrolled at Texas A&M on scholarship, set the NCAA outdoor 800 mark and ran the second-fastest 800 ever as a freshman.\", \"from\": 7095, \"to\": 7217, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7111, \"end\": 7116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas\", \"score\": 0.9999372684919878, \"rank\": 4.8022904408332596e-05, \"text\": \"Texas\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas\"}, {\"begin\": 7117, \"end\": 7120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Henson_Company_Lot\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.989436014995498e-48, \"text\": \"A&M\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Henson_Company_Lot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Henson_Company_Lot\"}, {\"begin\": 7145, \"end\": 7149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.939813045222535e-16, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI was at peace with myself,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says.\", \"from\": 7218, \"to\": 7261, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m blessed with this gift.\", \"from\": 7262, \"to\": 7294, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t take it for granted.\", \"from\": 7295, \"to\": 7325, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m here for a reason.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Sure, she had watched the Rio Games as a 14-year-old and thought,I want to be an Olympic champion.\", \"from\": 7326, \"to\": 7453, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But that quickly?\", \"from\": 7454, \"to\": 7471, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At 19?\", \"from\": 7472, \"to\": 7478, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mu didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t think like that.\", \"from\": 7479, \"to\": 7507, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe were just normal,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says.\", \"from\": 7508, \"to\": 7544, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cNormal, ordinary youth club.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Normal meant joy.\", \"from\": 7545, \"to\": 7598, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And joy meant speed.\", \"from\": 7599, \"to\": 7619, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Winning had never been Mu\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s problem.\", \"from\": 7621, \"to\": 7659, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Winningtoo oftenwould be.\", \"from\": 7660, \"to\": 7685, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When Mu qualified for the Tokyo Games, local officials hung a banner outside city hall in Trenton.\", \"from\": 7687, \"to\": 7785, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7692, \"end\": 7694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.844886024119947e-10, \"text\": \"Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\"}, {\"begin\": 7777, \"end\": 7784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\", \"score\": 0.8894944214207702, \"rank\": 0.1242341446081344, \"text\": \"Trenton\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many prepped for Olympic viewing parties and celebrated her as theirs, as them.\", \"from\": 7786, \"to\": 7865, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mu delivered, but in delivering, she paid a higher-than-expected toll.\", \"from\": 7866, \"to\": 7936, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two years after the Olympics she let slip in one interview what she had known, inside, ever since those magical Games concluded.This pressure was different.She had always embraced the gravity of competition but needed time to adjust to the unfathomable stress often baked into greatness, all the eyeballs and attention, flashing lights and clicking cameras, not to mention the negativity swamps known as social media.\", \"from\": 7938, \"to\": 8355, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Skeptics\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094there weren\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t many, but enough to catch her attention\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094began circling, especially after her performance at the worlds.\", \"from\": 8356, \"to\": 8488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Overwhelmed, she focused on the negative aspects of excellence, standards now so high they seemed impossible to meet.\", \"from\": 8490, \"to\": 8607, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t some top-five NFL draft pick.\", \"from\": 8608, \"to\": 8650, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8635, \"end\": 8638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"score\": 0.9999999991987352, \"rank\": 4.60281953113316e-10, \"text\": \"NFL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was a track star, a big deal in a niche space, largely ignored by mainstream sports fans outside of Olympic years.\", \"from\": 8651, \"to\": 8769, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But breaking through the track bubble, sprinting so fast as to attract year-round attention, didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t make things better.\", \"from\": 8770, \"to\": 8891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It made things worse.\", \"from\": 8892, \"to\": 8913, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt goes beyond just being a great athlete,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Mu says.\", \"from\": 8914, \"to\": 8971, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBecause, again, there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s expectations, there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s pressure; just eyes being put on you.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Whether she could take the figurative baton fromFelix, becoming not just a face of the U.S. team but the primary one, no longer seemed like a fair question.Felix\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s legacywas defined by longevity, consistency over not years but decades.\", \"from\": 8972, \"to\": 9304, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And there was Mu, fracturing, cracking, fed up\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094after a single, exceptional Olympics.\", \"from\": 9305, \"to\": 9391, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9319, \"end\": 9321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.844886024119947e-10, \"text\": \"Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cShe was,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Arceneaux says, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cin a space where it weighed on her.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Instead of running with joy, like she once did, Mu grew more and more serious, then more and more dark, the sentiment never clearer than in Budapest.\\u00c2  It was time for a break.\\u00c2  She started off with a real vacation\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094no running, no tracks.\", \"from\": 9393, \"to\": 9707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9515, \"end\": 9517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.844886024119947e-10, \"text\": \"Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the 2023 worlds she went back to Trenton, back to family and a simpler life, her commitments slimmed way down.\", \"from\": 9708, \"to\": 9824, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9747, \"end\": 9754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\", \"score\": 0.8894944214207702, \"rank\": 0.1242341446081344, \"text\": \"Trenton\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She visited a sibling in North Dakota.\", \"from\": 9825, \"to\": 9863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9850, \"end\": 9862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Dakota\", \"score\": 0.9972474879280626, \"rank\": 0.002760106766024367, \"text\": \"North Dakota\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Dakota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Dakota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She felt safe in both places, found comfort there.\", \"from\": 9864, \"to\": 9914, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mu got off social media, replacing online trolling with supportive, familiar voices.\", \"from\": 9915, \"to\": 9999, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She read the Bible and prayed daily.\", \"from\": 10000, \"to\": 10036, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She took walks, slowing down.\", \"from\": 10037, \"to\": 10066, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099d never done that before.\", \"from\": 10067, \"to\": 10098, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The break, she says, formed one long, deep breath.\", \"from\": 10100, \"to\": 10150, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Twice, while shopping in Santa Monica, strangers stopped her.\", \"from\": 10152, \"to\": 10213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10177, \"end\": 10189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santa_Monica_Boulevard\", \"score\": 0.9955564702597874, \"rank\": 0.004463345740644025, \"text\": \"Santa Monica\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santa_Monica_Boulevard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santa_Monica_Boulevard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One congratulated Mu on her performance in Budapest.\", \"from\": 10214, \"to\": 10266, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10257, \"end\": 10265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.745023976496267e-21, \"text\": \"Budapest\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The other asked if he could hug her, and\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0089\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0089of course he could!\", \"from\": 10267, \"to\": 10335, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t care how you do; we just love you,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he said, with no idea how much she needed his support.\", \"from\": 10336, \"to\": 10442, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Those positive interactions underscored her ratio of supporters to skeptics.\", \"from\": 10443, \"to\": 10519, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mu had been focused on the wrong people, the infinitely smaller segment.\", \"from\": 10520, \"to\": 10592, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Every day, she felt a pinch more centered, more grounded.\", \"from\": 10594, \"to\": 10651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She started to see that stretch for what it was\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094a time of transition, rather than a referendum on her track soul.\\u00c2  She still wanted to win, break records and run faster than ever before.\", \"from\": 10652, \"to\": 10841, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She still wanted to define her career by all she could accomplish.\", \"from\": 10842, \"to\": 10908, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Mu realized she ran fastest and won most when she ran happy.\", \"from\": 10909, \"to\": 10973, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Worrying about all the ancillary nonsense only made winning harder, less jubilant.\", \"from\": 10974, \"to\": 11056, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She shaped her new training schedule with intention: She would train year-round, but also build in regular breaks.\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00c2  Soon, Mu sensed the return of \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cmy true self.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d In the months and weeks that followed, the sadness infiltrating her joyful existence dripped away.\", \"from\": 11057, \"to\": 11324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11182, \"end\": 11184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.844886024119947e-10, \"text\": \"Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hope returned.\", \"from\": 11325, \"to\": 11339, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nerves dissipated.\", \"from\": 11340, \"to\": 11358, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She came to view what she overcame as central to her growth.\", \"from\": 11359, \"to\": 11419, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She returned to a more pragmatic approach, running like that 6-year-old in Trenton ran.\", \"from\": 11420, \"to\": 11507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11495, \"end\": 11502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\", \"score\": 0.8894944214207702, \"rank\": 0.1242341446081344, \"text\": \"Trenton\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When she did that, dominance no longer powered her search for purpose and fulfillment.\", \"from\": 11508, \"to\": 11594, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After the 2023 worlds, Arceneaux arranged a call with a track legend, one who happens to be married to Mu\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s coach.\", \"from\": 11596, \"to\": 11712, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jackie Joyner-Kersee competed at four Olympics and won a combined six medals, half of them gold, in the heptathlon and long jump.\", \"from\": 11713, \"to\": 11842, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11713, \"end\": 11733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jackie_Joyner-Kersee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jackie Joyner-Kersee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jackie_Joyner-Kersee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jackie_Joyner-Kersee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Joyner-Kersee reminded Mu that all the greats lost, slumped or, in the absence of either, faced increasing public pressure borne from lasting success.\", \"from\": 11843, \"to\": 11993, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The youngest among them, like Mu, were more likely to suffer from that.\", \"from\": 11994, \"to\": 12065, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But fearing that experience wouldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t do Mu any good.\", \"from\": 12066, \"to\": 12120, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mu would finish last season, Joyner-Kersee told her, showing their world \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cexactly who you are.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Once she was back on track, Mu had to get backon thetrack.\", \"from\": 12122, \"to\": 12281, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12122, \"end\": 12124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.844886024119947e-10, \"text\": \"Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\"}, {\"begin\": 12251, \"end\": 12253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.844886024119947e-10, \"text\": \"Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her coach suggested she run in a meet she hadn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t even thought about entering.\", \"from\": 12282, \"to\": 12361, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She sent one teammate a text message, asking that they pray.\", \"from\": 12362, \"to\": 12422, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She entered the Prefontaine Classic last September, a surprise to nearly everyone in her sport given how sparingly she had run in 2023.\", \"from\": 12423, \"to\": 12558, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She then set a blistering pace, jockeying with Hodgkinson for positioning and then passing her rival on the final straightaway.\", \"from\": 12559, \"to\": 12686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12606, \"end\": 12616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.9995230677747003, \"rank\": 0.00047715979820798815, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She won, holding onto first in a race where the top three women each broke their national record, including Mu, who finished in 1:54.97.\", \"from\": 12687, \"to\": 12823, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12795, \"end\": 12797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.844886024119947e-10, \"text\": \"Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In December, on a Zoom call, with the Olympics only seven months away, Mu sounded transformed.\", \"from\": 12825, \"to\": 12919, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12896, \"end\": 12898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.844886024119947e-10, \"text\": \"Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI can see everything that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s happening around me,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she said.\", \"from\": 12920, \"to\": 12986, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cMy vision, early on, used to be so small.\", \"from\": 12987, \"to\": 13031, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now I see the bigger picture.\", \"from\": 13032, \"to\": 13061, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m going to appreciate this more.\", \"from\": 13062, \"to\": 13098, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Oh, my God, I have so much gratitude.\", \"from\": 13099, \"to\": 13136, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m just so happy\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094for, like, everything that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s getting ready to come, what\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s right at my feet.\", \"from\": 13137, \"to\": 13239, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m just happy to be able to run again.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Mu knows who she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s running for and who she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s not.\", \"from\": 13240, \"to\": 13339, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She trusts her coach and their training.\", \"from\": 13340, \"to\": 13380, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She has never been more consistent, more level, more balanced.\", \"from\": 13381, \"to\": 13443, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her relationship to track has never been stronger or healthier.\", \"from\": 13444, \"to\": 13507, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Arceneaux noticed Mu was running with joy again, that style of competing, he says, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cthat makes her adorable and why fans will fall in love with her\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d this summer, when the Games unfold.\", \"from\": 13508, \"to\": 13696, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13526, \"end\": 13528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.844886024119947e-10, \"text\": \"Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe best part is,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Mu says, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m enjoying it in a different way, not on a bad roll but genuinely, like, happy.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Every day since Budapest has pointed Mu towardParis.\", \"from\": 13698, \"to\": 13874, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13722, \"end\": 13724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.844886024119947e-10, \"text\": \"Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\"}, {\"begin\": 13838, \"end\": 13846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.745023976496267e-21, \"text\": \"Budapest\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She rested for the Olympics, trained for the Olympics and dreamt of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 13875, \"to\": 13956, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But throughout, she also lowered her expectations.\", \"from\": 13957, \"to\": 14007, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She continued to stay off social media.\", \"from\": 14008, \"to\": 14047, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Continued to break when necessary.\", \"from\": 14048, \"to\": 14082, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sure, the nerves and anxiety still occasionally bubbled to the surface.\", \"from\": 14083, \"to\": 14154, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And when they did, Mu told herself, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWho cares?\", \"from\": 14155, \"to\": 14204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14174, \"end\": 14176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.844886024119947e-10, \"text\": \"Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m ready again.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Ready to compete.\", \"from\": 14205, \"to\": 14245, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ready to win.\", \"from\": 14246, \"to\": 14259, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ready to fall.\", \"from\": 14260, \"to\": 14274, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Doesn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t matter.\", \"from\": 14275, \"to\": 14292, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Never did.\", \"from\": 14293, \"to\": 14303, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 14305, \"to\": 14331, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Greg Bishop is a senior writer for Sports Illustrated who has covered every kind of sport and every major event across six continents for more than two decades.\", \"from\": 14332, \"to\": 14556, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14396, \"end\": 14407, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greg_Bishop\", \"score\": 0.9999950627965526, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Greg Bishop\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greg_Bishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greg_Bishop\"}, {\"begin\": 14431, \"end\": 14449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1798763148849578e-41, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\",